==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enterobacteriaceae
<hw>En`ter*o*bac`te*ri*a"ce*ae</hw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧n`t⟦etil⟧r*⟦osl⟧*b⟦acr⟧k`t⟦emac⟧r*⟦emac⟧*⟦amac⟧"s⟦emac⟧*⟦emac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Microbiol.)</fld> <def>a natural family of
rod-shaped gram-negative bacteria, most of which occur normally or
pathogenically in intestines of humans and other animals, and some of
which grow in plants. The type genus is <gen>Escherichia</gen>. They are
aerobic and facultatively anaerobic, and may be motile or non-motile.
Most are easily cultured on artificial growth media. Both pathogenic and
non-pathogenic strains exist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>enterobacterial</ent>⟦br⟧
